SIMPLE: nucleolus
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nucleolus
<hw>Nu*cle"o*lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Nucleoli</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a little nut, dim. of
<ets>nucleus</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A little nucleus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A small rounded body contained in
the nucleus of a cell or a protozoan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It was termed by Agassiz the <xex>entoblast</xex>. In
the protozoa, where it may be situated on one side of the nucleus, it is
sometimes called the <xex>endoplastule</xex>, and is supposed to be
concerned in the male part of the reproductive process. See
<er>Nucleus</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nucleon</ent>⟦br⟧
